---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Contact | The Lawn Guide"
  description="Get in touch with The Lawn Guide editorial team. Questions, feedback, corrections, partnerships, and press enquiries."
>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 md:py-20">
    <header class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-terracotta-600 font-medium mb-4">Contact</p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-6xl text-forest-900 leading-tight tracking-tight">
        Get in touch.
      </h1>
    </header>

    <div class="prose">
      <p class="text-xl text-ink-700 leading-relaxed mb-8 font-serif italic">
        We read everything sent to us. Reply times vary depending on what you're asking about, but everyone gets a response.
      </p>

      <h2>General questions and feedback</h2>
      <p>
        Email <a href="mailto:hello@lawnguide.co.uk">hello@lawnguide.co.uk</a> for general questions, article feedback, suggestions for things we should cover, or anything else that doesn't fit a more specific category below.
      </p>

      <h2>Corrections</h2>
      <p>
        If we've published something factually wrong, please tell us. Email <a href="mailto:hello@lawnguide.co.uk">hello@lawnguide.co.uk</a> with "Correction" in the subject line and we'll review and update the article.
      </p>
      <p>
        We take corrections seriously. Honest correction is part of being a publication worth trusting, and the alternative is publishing wrong information indefinitely.
      </p>

      <h2>Product reviews and testing</h2>
      <p>
        If you represent a brand and want us to consider a product for review, email <a href="mailto:hello@lawnguide.co.uk">hello@lawnguide.co.uk</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        A few things to know before you write:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>We can't promise to cover every product sent to us. Our content calendar is planned around what readers are searching for, not what we receive in the post</li>
        <li>Receiving a product for testing does not guarantee a positive review. We've returned products we couldn't recommend, and we'll continue doing so</li>
        <li>We disclose product receipt in any article where it's relevant. This is a hard editorial rule</li>
        <li>We don't accept paid placements, sponsored content, or commission-influenced reviews</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Partnerships and affiliate enquiries</h2>
      <p>
        For affiliate programme partnerships and similar commercial enquiries, email <a href="mailto:hello@lawnguide.co.uk">hello@lawnguide.co.uk</a> with "Partnership" in the subject line.
      </p>
      <p>
        We work with major affiliate networks including Awin, Amazon Associates UK, and direct programmes with UK lawn care brands. Our affiliate disclosure is on the <a href="/affiliate-disclosure">disclosure page</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Press and media</h2>
      <p>
        For press enquiries, expert comment requests, or media partnerships, email <a href="mailto:hello@lawnguide.co.uk">hello@lawnguide.co.uk</a> with "Press" in the subject line.
      </p>
      <p>
        We're happy to comment on UK lawn care, gardening trends, and seasonal issues for journalists working on relevant stories.
      </p>

      <h2>Privacy and data</h2>
      <p>
        For questions about how we handle data, deletion requests under UK GDPR, or anything else covered by our <a href="/privacy">privacy policy</a>, email <a href="mailto:hello@lawnguide.co.uk">hello@lawnguide.co.uk</a>. We respond to all GDPR requests within 30 days.
      </p>

      <h2>What we can't help with</h2>
      <p>
        We're an editorial publication, not a retailer or service provider. A few things we can't do:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Personal lawn consultations or in-garden advice (use our content for guidance, or hire a local lawn care professional for hands-on help)</li>
        <li>Customer service for products you've bought from retailers we link to (contact the retailer directly)</li>
        <li>Recommendations for specific products outside what we've reviewed (we only recommend what we know, which is what's covered in our reviews)</li>
        <li>Diagnosing specific lawn problems from photos by email (the diagnostic guides on the site are designed to help you self-diagnose)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Postal address</h2>
      <p>
        For physical correspondence or product samples, email <a href="mailto:hello@lawnguide.co.uk">hello@lawnguide.co.uk</a> first to confirm a delivery address. We don't publish a permanent postal address publicly to avoid unsolicited deliveries.
      </p>

      <p class="text-sm text-ink-500 mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-forest-200/60">
        The Lawn Guide is operated as a sole trader business based in the United Kingdom. For data protection purposes, the data controller is the operator of this site and can be contacted at <a href="mailto:hello@lawnguide.co.uk" class="text-terracotta-600 hover:text-terracotta-700">hello@lawnguide.co.uk</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>